    "summary": "While recovering tax and customs duties in previous jobs (on both national and European level), I learned that it is necessary to monitor individual debtors to keep the normal flows of tax revenue for government activities running. Not safeguarding recovery from individual debtors, would simply mean that other taxpayers need to pay more. \n\nWhen working for the European Commission, I found out that the same same applied for the recovery of so called Traditional Own Resources on the European level. I learned that, also here, it was necessary to monitor individual Member States to keep the usual budget flows running. No proper follow-up of financial claims from the Commisson, would simply mean that the European taxpayer must pay more.\n\nAfter having worked for the Commission for eight years, I have now decided to find out whether it is possible to further contribute to the European project from a more personal perspective. Actually, I would like to assist EU Member States' administrations in becoming (more) EU-proof. I am therefore now taking contact with all concerned to see what possibilities exist. \n\nI consider it challenging \u00e1nd rewarding to work in a field where one is able to contribute to safeguard the daily budgetary flows in the public domain; both on the national and the international level. Working in a multi-cultural environment adds, of course, an interesting aspect to this work \u2018for the common good\u2019. The public benefit of all this is even more rewarding, where one is able to use his previous work experience for improving budget linked procedures (managing them in a more strategic, systematic or less costly way) be they on the national or international level.\n\nYou can easily contact me on: davids.hans@gmail.com or visit the website referred to above.\n\nSpecialties: Language skills in Dutch, English, German, French, Italian and Spanish. \nInterest in talent profiles of persons and companies and their individual \u00b4destinations\u00b4. \nMilitary education.",
